title: New York Declares State of Emergency Over Polio After Virus Found In Wastewater
content: New York declared a state of emergency over polio in an effort to boost vaccination rates after evidence of the virus's spread mounted when it was found in wastewater samples.

title: JEE Advanced 2022 Result Out; Pass Percentage Dips To 26.17 Per Cent
details: Written by Arnab Mitra  | Sunday September 11, 2022
content: JEE Advanced 2022 Result: A total of 26.17 per cent candidates qualified in the engineering entrance this year, last year the pass percentage was 30 per cent

title: 1 Killed, 20 Injured And Several Missing After Surat Factory Fire
details: Press Trust of India   | Sunday September 11, 2022, Surat
content: A worker was killed, 20 others were injured and three went missing after a major fire broke out in a chemical factory in Gujarat's Surat city, officials said on Sunday.

title: "Very Poor Shot Selection": Former Pakistan Captain Slams Babar Azam And Co's Batting Against Sri Lanka

title: Nawabi Kababi Offers A Slice Of Old Delhi Through Its Lip-Smacking Kebabs

title: 12 Kg Gold Worth Rs 5.38 Crore Seized At Mumbai Airport
details: Asian News International   | Sunday September 11, 2022, Mumbai
content: Twelve-kilogram gold valued at Rs 5.38 Crore has been seized by the officers of the Mumbai Airport customs on Sunday.

title: Video: Doctor, Son Say Beaten For Delay In Opening Clinic Door
details: Reported by Sunil Singh, Edited by Supriti David  | Sunday September 11, 2022, Maharashtra
content: A doctor was beaten by a group of men in Maharashtra's Baramati on September 6 after he opened the clinic door late to let them in, police said.

title: 7 Of Top 10 Most Valued Firms' Market Value Reaches Rs 1.33 Lakh Crore
details: Press Trust of India   | Sunday September 11, 2022, New Delhi
content: The combined market valuation of seven of the top 10 most-valued firms climbed Rs 1,33,746.87 crore last week amid a firm trend in equities, with Tata Consultancy Services (TCS), Reliance Industries and Infosys leading the pack of gainers.

title: India Women vs England Women: "We Forcefully Played," Says Harmanpreet Kaur After Defeat In 1st T20I
details: Press Trust of India   | Sunday September 11, 2022
content: India women's team captain Harmanpreet Kaur said the side "forcefully played" in wet conditions in the first T20 International against England here, resulting in a nine-wicket defeat for the tourists.

title: Fake Invoice Racket Worth Rs 132 Crore Busted In Mumbai, 1 Arrested
details: Asian News International   | Sunday September 11, 2022, Mumbai
content: The Bhiwandi Commisionerate of Central Goods and Services Tax (CGST) in Mumbai Zone busted a fake invoice racket worth Rs 132 crore and availing/passing on Input Tax credit of Rs 23 crore.

title: Video: Muffled Church Bells Toll For The First Time In 70 Years Across UK In Tribute To Queen Elizabeth
details: Edited by Bhavya Sukheja  | Sunday September 11, 2022
content: On Friday, churches across the United Kingdom marked their respect for Queen Elizabeth II by ringing their bells - specifically with muffles in order to create a more solemn sound.

title: What England Pacer Ollie Robinson Said About Singing New UK National Anthem
content: Ollie Robinson revealed England cricketers had worries about singing the new British national anthem at the Oval on Saturday in case they got the words wrong.
